OL,3,CHow a university scholarship became a
OL,4,Cbeacon of hope for one man from Gaza
OL,6,F"It was a surprising moment. The most
OL,7,Fbeautiful one. I just prayed with my
OL,8,Ffamily. It was like the war stopped
OL,9,Fthat moment, we were celebrating," he
OL,10,Frecalls as his face lights up.
OL,12,FThe 27-year-old is now studying for a
OL,13,FMaster's in Infectious Disease at the
OL,14,FUniversity of Glasgow.
OL,16,F"Lots of children lost their limbs;
OL,17,Fthey haven't had access to medicines
OL,18,For healthcare. It's dark, very dark
OL,19,Factually, but we are trying to do
OL,20,Fsomething meaningful," he said.
