OL,3,CHow a university scholarship became a
OL,4,Cbeacon of hope for one man from Gaza
OL,6,F"I don't recognise our existence here
OL,7,Fin the UK as an escape but as a
OL,8,Fresponsibility," he said.
OL,10,FThe words of support from his family
OL,11,Fare always in his head.
OL,13,F"They tell me we are proud of you and
OL,14,Fthat our pride is not where you are in
OL,15,Fbut in what you will give back to your
OL,16,Fcommunity and whole world," Mohammed
OL,17,Fadded.
OL,19,FAmid the trauma back home, one
OL,20,Fstudent's determination to build hope
OL,21,Ffrom Gaza's despair shines out.
